<div class="devsite-article-body clearfix
">































































<p>This page lists all languages supported by Cloud Speech-to-Text. Language is
specified within a recognition request&#39;s
<a href="/speech-to-text/v2/docs/reference/rpc/google.cloud.speech.v2#recognizer"><code translate="no" dir="ltr">languageCodes</code></a>
parameter. For more information about sending a recognition request and
specifying the language of the transcription, see the
<a href="/speech-to-text/v2/docs/how-to">how-to guides</a> about performing speech
recognition. For more information about the
<a href="/speech-to-text/v2/docs/adaptation-model#classes">class tokens</a> available for
each language, see the
<a href="/speech-to-text/v2/docs/class-tokens">class tokens page</a>.</p>









<cloudx-free-trial-eligible-content>
<slot slot="eligible">
<div class="cloud-section__spacer">
<h2 class="hide-from-toc" id="try-it-for-yourself" data-text=" Try it for yourself " tabindex="-1">
Try it for yourself
</h2>

<p>
If you're new to Google Cloud, create an account to evaluate how
Speech-to-Text performs in real-world
scenarios. New customers also get $300 in free credits to run, test, and
deploy workloads.
</p>


































































































































<a href="https://console.cloud.google.com/freetrial"
class="cloud-button cloud-button--primary"
track-type="button"
track-name="
Try Speech-to-Text free
"
track-metadata-eventdetail="https://console.cloud.google.com/freetrial"
track-metadata-modifier="primary"
track-metadata-anchor_text="
Try Speech-to-Text free
"
track-metadata-href="https://console.cloud.google.com/freetrial"
referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade"
>
Try Speech-to-Text free</a>




</div>
</slot>
<slot slot="ineligible">
</slot>
</cloudx-free-trial-eligible-content>

<p>The table below lists the models available for each language. Cloud
Speech-to-Text offers multiple
<a href="https://cloud.google.com/speech-to-text/v2/docs/basics#select-model">recognition models</a>,
each tuned to different audio types.</p>

<p>Some languages are supported by additional models which are optimized for
additional audio types: <strong>telephony</strong>.</p>

<p>Use only the language codes shown in the following table. The following language
codes are officially maintained and monitored externally by Google. Using other
language codes can result in breaking changes.</p>

<p>Filter on supported features:
<form id="features-filters">
<table>
<tr>
<td>
<div>
<input type="checkbox" id="checkbox-toggle-all" class="toggle-all">

</div>
<div>
<input type="checkbox" id="profanity" value="prof">
<label for="profanity">Profanity filter</label>
</div>
<div>
<input type="checkbox" id="spoken_punctuation" value="spunc">
<label for="spoken_punctuation">Spoken punctuation</label>
<span>(<a href="/speech-to-text/v2/docs/spoken-punctuation-emojis">add spoken punctuation</a>)</span>
</div>
<div>
<input type="checkbox" id="spoken_emojis" value="semj">
<label for="spoken_emojis">Spoken emojis</label>
<span>(<a href="/speech-to-text/v2/docs/spoken-punctuation-emojis">add spoken emojis</a>)</span>
</div>
</td>

<div>

</div>
